She’s a lot like you used to be.

82
00:08:29,642 --> 00:08:31,967
- Like me?
- Yeah.

83
00:08:32,061 --> 00:08:34,552
What do you mean?

84
00:08:34,647 --> 00:08:37,648
Don’t you remember
what you did to my grandmother?

85
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:41,184
- I didn’t do anything to her.
- You said the same thing then.

86
00:08:41,278 --> 00:08:42,903
You said that Fred did it.

87
00:08:45,449 --> 00:08:47,738
Drop Dead Fred.

88
00:08:50,412 --> 00:08:52,451
Grandma Bunce!

89
00:08:59,045 --> 00:09:02,960
- Drop Dead Fred.
- I used to pretend I had an imaginary friend.

90
00:09:03,049 --> 00:09:05,089
No one believed me.

91
00:09:05,176 --> 00:09:11,012
Do you remember the time you and Fred
came over to borrow my father’s electric shaver?

92
00:09:11,099 --> 00:09:13,138
Yes.

93
00:09:26,781 --> 00:09:30,031
- You must have thought I was crazy.
- Not at all.

94
00:09:30,117 --> 00:09:33,901
