No, not always.

97
00:09:41,754 --> 00:09:43,793
Only when my mother was...

98
00:09:44,590 --> 00:09:46,629
Well, you know.

99
00:09:46,717 --> 00:09:49,920
Hey, we were all a
little afraid of your mother.

100
00:09:51,555 --> 00:09:54,472
Not Fred. No,
he always stood up for me.

101
00:09:54,558 --> 00:09:58,009
That’s what friends are for,
even imaginary ones.

102
00:10:07,570 --> 00:10:11,319
I realise you’re feeling
pretty conflicted right now.

103
00:10:12,450 --> 00:10:14,277
I feel awful.

104
00:10:14,369 --> 00:10:19,992
I did this self-actualising workshop
and they taught us that pain is your friend.

105
00:10:20,082 --> 00:10:22,490
- Pain makes you interesting.
- Janie.

106
00:10:22,585 --> 00:10:25,040
Look at Elvis.

107
00:10:25,129 --> 00:10:27,168
Yeah, but didn’t Elvis kill himself?

108
00:10:27,256 --> 00:10:29,628
Yes, but before that he was interesting.

109
00:10:29,717 --> 00:10:32,172
I want you to do some affirmations with me.

110
00:10:32,261 --> 00:10:33,885
- Janie.
- Just do it.

111
00:10:33,971 --> 00:10:36,094
