00:42:38,506 --> 00:42:41,128
What? Faster?

484
00:42:41,217 --> 00:42:43,257
Okey-dokey.

485
00:42:59,652 --> 00:43:04,480
This way! Captain Fred’s in charge!

486
00:43:09,578 --> 00:43:13,279
Drown the fishes! Kill all the parrots!

487
00:43:32,017 --> 00:43:34,140
What is that water doing there?

488
00:43:34,227 --> 00:43:36,599
- What water?
- That water.

489
00:43:36,688 --> 00:43:40,520
I don’t know.
What are your thoughts?

490
00:43:40,608 --> 00:43:42,648
Whoa!

491
00:43:43,778 --> 00:43:45,818
Man the lifeboats!

492
00:44:10,387 --> 00:44:12,925
Excuse me a minute, would you?

493
00:44:19,646 --> 00:44:22,896
- Now what’s happened?
- I have some bad news for you.

494
00:44:22,983 --> 00:44:24,560
More?

495
00:44:25,777 --> 00:44:28,399
Remember your house?

496
00:44:28,488 --> 00:44:29,899
Yeah.

497
00:44:29,990 --> 00:44:34,118
It... It sank.

498
00:44:34,202 --> 00:44:36,242
What?

499
00:44:36,329 --> 00:44:38,902
Er, I didn’t mean for it...

500
00:44:38,998 --> 00:44:41,572
Drop Dead Fred just...

501
00:44:42,919 --> 00:44:44,828
He was way out of control.

502
00:44:44,921 --> 00:44:48,870
Do you think I have an
imaginary-friend clause in my insurance?

503
00:44:48,966 --> 00:44:51,208
Janie, I’m so sorry.

504
00:44:51,302 --> 00:44:55,252
- Everything I own is on that boat.
- It’s all still there.

505
00:44:55,348 --> 00:44:59,262
It’s just... not so near the top of the water.

506
00:45:01,854 --> 00:45:05,223
You always tell me to look on
the bright side of things.

507
00:45:05,316 --> 00:45:08,566
What would that be in
this particular situation?

508
00:45:11,822 --> 00:45:13,649
There he is.

509
00:45:14,491 --> 00:45:16,318
- Murray?
- No.

510
00:45:17,035 --> 00:45:18,660
- Not...
- Yes.

511
00:45:18,745 --> 00:45:25,033
How about the silverware service? A complete
mystery to me but was completely ruined.

512
00:45:25,127 --> 00:45:26,918
Any response?

513
00:45:27,003 --> 00:45:30,787
