What does it look like I’m doing?

530
00:46:44,912 --> 00:46:48,495
- There’s nobody there.
- He’s invisible, idiot.

531
00:46:49,542 --> 00:46:52,792
Die! You’re dead, little man!

532
00:46:52,878 --> 00:46:54,586
That’s for the boat!

533
00:46:54,672 --> 00:46:59,914
That’s for ruining the one schtup I get
a month when Murray’s wife is out of town!

534
00:47:06,809 --> 00:47:08,931
It’s very hot in here, isn’t it?

535
00:47:20,030 --> 00:47:25,272
This is stupid. We ought to be in a shop
that sells harpoons and nets and hammers.

536
00:47:25,368 --> 00:47:29,069
- What for?
- We could harpoon Charles through the head,

537
00:47:29,164 --> 00:47:33,078
drag him home and hit him with the hammer
till he agrees to come back.

538
00:47:33,168 --> 00:47:35,955
- Harpoon him through the head?
- Brilliant.

539
00:47:36,045 --> 00:47:39,497
- It’s not going to work.
- How many times have you tried it?

540
00:47:39,590 --> 00:47:41,963
- We’re not five any more.
- I know.

541
00:47:43,636 --> 00:47:47,883
- This would be good for the wine gala.
- It looks like a big bruise.

542
00:47:48,766 --> 00:47:52,466
- I’m going to be late for lunch.
- Who are you having lunch with?

543
00:47:52,561 --> 00:47:55,396
An old friend and I don’t mean you.

544
00:47:55,481 --> 00:47:57,520
You’re not invited.

545
00:47:58,651 --> 00:48:00,690
Why not?

546
00:48:00,778 --> 00:48:03,019
We always do everything together.

547
00:48:04,198 --> 00:48:06,024
Thank you.

548
00:48:07,075 --> 00:48:11,203
- This is a great place.
- It’s Charles’s favourite restaurant.

549
00:48:11,288 --> 00:48:13,660
Oh.

550
00:48:13,749 --> 00:48:15,788
You cut your hair.

551
00:48:15,876 --> 00:48:19,291
- Yeah. Charles is going to hate it.
- You look beautiful.

552
00:48:19,379 --> 00:48:23,922
- Just relax. Let’s have a nice lunch.
- OK.

553
00:48:24,009 --> 00:48:25,669
Hi. What’s happening?

554
00:48:27,804 --> 00:48:31,220
Oh, no. Mickey fart pants.
Who let him grow up?

555
00:48:31,307 --> 00:48:34,094
- Go away.
- What?

556
00:48:36,562 --> 00:48:39,812
- I’m sorry.
- No, don’t apologise.

557
00:48:39,899 --> 00:48:43,849
I love being with you.
I love the way you cut your hair.

558
00:48:43,945 --> 00:48:46,021
I love the way you sink houseboats.

559
00:48:46,113 --> 00:48:50,740
Look at him. He’s still talking about love.
I always said you should be a girl.

560
00:48:52,912 --> 00:48:59,080
You know, some people believe
that you really never ever fall out of love.

561
00:48:59,168 --> 00:49:04,209
Oh! This isn’t like when we were five.
We’re grown-ups now, so piss off.

562
00:49:04,298 --> 00:49:07,832
I’d like to know more about
the grown-up Mickey Bunce.

563
00:49:07,926 --> 00:49:09,966
OK, I...

564
00:49:10,846 --> 00:49:16,848
Well... I know how much you...
hate the word divorce

565
00:49:16,935 --> 00:49:21,063
but after mine I had to get back
into the whole dating...

566
00:49:24,275 --> 00:49:26,102
game.

567
00:49:32,367 --> 00:49:35,652
- Yes, Mickey, go on.
- Yes, Mickey, go on.

568
00:49:36,579 --> 00:49:38,619
OK. Erm...

569
00:49:40,249 --> 00:49:42,538
See that woman over there?

570
00:49:44,170 --> 00:49:45,878
Mm-hm.

571
00:49:47,631 --> 00:49:50,336
