572
00:49:50,426 --> 00:49:56,345
It was funny. I didn’t know whether I should
hold her hand when we walked down the street

573
00:49:56,432 --> 00:49:58,471
or give her a kiss good night.

574
00:49:59,852 --> 00:50:02,722
I felt like I was back in high school again.

575
00:50:07,651 --> 00:50:09,690
Why did you do that?

576
00:50:10,529 --> 00:50:13,814
- I didn’t.
- No, you did. I saw you do that.

577
00:50:17,160 --> 00:50:20,363
I did, didn’t I? To get the waiter’s attention.

578
00:50:20,455 --> 00:50:22,578
Well, I don’t think that works.

579
00:50:23,917 --> 00:50:26,158
Maybe that does work.

580
00:50:26,252 --> 00:50:28,292
Your lunch.

581
00:50:29,088 --> 00:50:31,128
And your lunch, sir.

582
00:50:31,841 --> 00:50:33,964
This table leg must be loose again.

583
00:50:41,976 --> 00:50:43,600
Peekaboo.

584
00:50:44,478 --> 00:50:48,262
Peekaboo, yeah.
I play that with Natalie all the time.

585
00:50:53,195 --> 00:50:55,484
Oh, yeah...

586
00:50:55,572 --> 00:50:57,612
- Smells good.
- Mm!

587
00:51:11,379 --> 00:51:13,787
OK. Why did you do that?

588
00:51:13,882 --> 00:51:15,625
Disgusting!

589
00:51:15,717 --> 00:51:17,508
I’m crazy.

590
00:51:17,594 --> 00:51:21,128
You are crazy in the most wonderful way.

591
00:51:21,222 --> 00:51:26,014
God, I wish I could be like that.
I wish I could do those kind of things.

592
00:51:28,396 --> 00:51:30,435
What the hell.

593
00:51:33,734 --> 00:51:35,774
Hey, buddy.

594
00:51:39,782 --> 00:51:43,732
- Uh-oh!
- You don’t throw spaghetti in my restaurant.

595
00:51:43,828 --> 00:51:45,867
Fine. You do it.

596
00:51:47,206 --> 00:51:50,290
You and the Puttanesca woman, out of here.

597
00:51:50,376 --> 00:51:52,831
I like him a lot better than I used to.

598
00:51:53,712 --> 00:51:55,954
- Take it easy.
- You’re out of here.

599
00:51:56,048 --> 00:51:59,547
- It was a joke. You guys should loosen up.
- Out!

600
00:52:00,385 --> 00:52:02,627
- What is Puttanesca?
- My dress.

601
00:52:02,721 --> 00:52:05,342
I’ll get it.
I’d like to. What the hell.

602
00:52:05,432 --> 00:52:07,839
Amigos.

603
00:52:07,934 --> 00:52:10,390
- Having fun?
- Come on, buddy.

604
00:52:11,855 --> 00:52:14,725
That was great.
That make you feel better?

605
00:52:14,816 --> 00:52:19,063
No. First you sink Janie’s houseboat.
What you did in that restaurant.

606
00:52:19,154 --> 00:52:22,404
- All you do is smash things up.
- What’s wrong with that?

607
00:52:22,490 --> 00:52:25,028
Nothing, except you’re ruining my life.

608
00:52:27,120 --> 00:52:31,616
Your problem is you’re no fun anymore.
You’ve turned into your mother.

609
00:52:31,707 --> 00:52:37,212
You are so sick. You know what?
I don’t want an imaginary friend any more.

610
00:52:37,296 --> 00:52:40,546
Do you see what you’re doing to me?
I’m talking to myself.

611
00:52:40,633 --> 00:52:44,761
You’re driving me crazy.
Please just get out of my life.

612
00:52:44,845 --> 00:52:50,800
All right, fine, I’m going and you’re never
going to see me again ever. Bye.

613
00:53:38,564 --> 00:53:40,603
I asked you nicely.

614
00:53:40,691 --> 00:53:42,731
Shh!

615
00:53:53,120 --> 00:53:55,159
Somebody call security.

616
00:53:55,247 --> 00:53:57,286
I’m so sorry.

617
00:53:58,625 --> 00:54:00,285
I’m...

618
00:54:01,628 --> 00:54:06,337
You play such an expensive violin
in a shopping mall?

619
00:54:06,424 --> 00:54:08,251
Where? What?

620
00:54:08,343 --> 00:54:11,593
I’m just getting my bag. I’m fine, Mother.

621
00:54:11,680 --> 00:54:15,463
How can you say that
when you have conversations with thin air?

622
00:54:15,558 --> 00:54:18,393
Not thin air, Drop Dead Fred.

623
00:54:18,478 --> 00:54:20,850
- Don’t mention his name.
- Sorry.

624
00:54:21,898 --> 00:54:25,646
You may have Drop Dead Fred.
I have Dr Ryland.

625
00:54:31,490 --> 00:54:35,618
Elizabeth, please have a seat outside.
I need a word with your mother.

626
00:54:36,412 --> 00:54:39,697
That’s the piece, Matthew.
You’ve finished it.

627
00:54:50,467 --> 00:54:56,007
I’m really sorry. I didn’t know I was going
to get you into so much trouble.

628
00:54:56,098 --> 00:55:00,475
So what did the doctor say?
Are you insane or what?

629
00:55:03,313 --> 00:55:05,352
Did they give you a lobotomy?

630
00:55:09,694 --> 00:55:11,734
He’s very good with children.

631
00:55:13,364 --> 00:55:14,989
Oh.

632
00:55:15,074 --> 00:55:21,444
He’s one of the country’s leading experts
in dealing with the imaginary-friend syndrome.

633
00:55:22,957 --> 00:55:25,578
Your child has one, too, huh?

634
00:55:25,668 --> 00:55:27,708
I don’t have a child.

635
00:55:27,795 --> 00:55:29,254
Oh?

636
00:55:29,338 --> 00:55:31,794
- Well, who’s in there?
- My mother.

637
00:55:31,882 --> 00:55:34,254
Oh!

638
00:55:34,343 --> 00:55:36,881
- Which one of you is...
- Me.

639
00:55:36,971 --> 00:55:39,640
- Let’s go.
- I’ll leave when I want to.

640
00:55:39,723 --> 00:55:41,467
OK, fine.

641
00:55:41,558 --> 00:55:44,643
OK, I was just asking.
Just trying to be nice.

642
00:55:58,200 --> 00:56:00,821
Go to Hell Herman! Argh!

643
00:56:00,911 --> 00:56:03,698
Fred! Argh!

644
00:56:03,788 --> 00:56:06,077
Punch me.

645
00:56:06,166 --> 00:56:07,576
Hey, hey!

646
00:56:07,667 --> 00:56:09,873
Yaah!

647
00:56:09,961 --> 00:56:12,534
Hey, Fred!

648
00:56:12,630 --> 00:56:15,667
- Velcro Head!
- Yaah!

649
00:56:15,758 --> 00:56:18,296
Brrrrrrr!

650
00:56:19,846 --> 00:56:21,423
What are you doing?

651
00:56:23,516 --> 00:56:25,555
I am playing with my friends.

652
00:56:28,813 --> 00:56:32,098
Hey, Freddy. Hi, guys!

653
00:56:32,191 --> 00:56:34,230
- Graggy.
- Hey, Fred, hold this.

654
00:56:38,781 --> 00:56:41,651
That’s so Namby Pamby.

655
00:56:41,742 --> 00:56:43,781
You called?

656
00:56:46,663 --> 00:56:48,703
Namby Pamby!

657
00:56:48,790 --> 00:56:50,748
Whoo!

658
00:56:50,834 --> 00:56:55,626
This is great. The whole gang’s here.
Let’s have a sick contest!

659
00:57:10,687 --> 00:57:14,933
Hey, watch this. Charge!

660
00:57:22,823 --> 00:57:25,279
Cuckoo! Cuckoo!

661
00:57:25,368 --> 00:57:26,992
Oooh!

662
00:57:27,078 --> 00:57:29,117
Very nice.

663
00:57:29,205 --> 00:57:33,202
Nine, maybe ten. I love it.

664
00:57:33,292 --> 00:57:35,331
- Not bad, huh?
- Beautiful.

665
00:57:37,629 --> 00:57:41,045
Let her take these after meals and before bed.

666
00:57:41,133 --> 00:57:43,671
- Are there any side effects?
- None.

667
00:57:43,760 --> 00:57:48,173
They just neutralise that part
of the brain which is malfunctioning.

668
00:57:48,265 --> 00:57:50,304
How did it come to this?

669
00:57:50,392 --> 00:57:53,393
She’s regressed to where these children are.

670
00:57:54,521 --> 00:57:56,560
Elizabeth.

671
00:58:01,319 --> 00:58:07,155
- Well, I’ve got to go, so I’ll see you chickens later.
- Fred. Not the pills.

672
00:58:07,242 --> 00:58:11,405
Why not? Do they make you sick or stupid?
I’ll take them. I’m Fred.

673
00:58:11,496 --> 00:58:14,532
You don’t want to
let her take the green ones.

674
00:58:14,624 --> 00:58:17,328
- Why not?
- Remember Go-Go Mouth?

675
00:58:17,418 --> 00:58:19,458
Yeah.

676
00:58:29,513 --> 00:58:33,012
- Don’t worry about me.
- No, no, F...

677
00:58:47,197 --> 00:58:49,237
Here we are.

678
00:58:49,324 --> 00:58:53,701
Now, I want you to
eat all your vegetables.

679
00:58:53,787 --> 00:58:55,826
- Yes.
- Yes what?

680
00:58:56,665 --> 00:58:58,823
- Yes, thank you.
- That’s better.

681
00:58:59,793 --> 00:59:03,790
We’re going to be great friends, Mrs Cronin.
I can see that.

682
00:59:06,549 --> 00:59:08,589
I’ll be right back.

683
00:59:20,229 --> 00:59:25,769
Don’t eat the napkin, dear. I’ve got
a black belt and I could break you like that.

684
00:59:25,860 --> 00:59:30,652
You’re going to behave.
Conscious or unconscious, it’s all the same to me.

685
00:59:31,782 --> 00:59:36,278
Whoo! I like her.
She is good. She is awfully good.

686
00:59:37,287 --> 00:59:39,529
I’ll be back in a moment with your pill.

687
00:59:39,623 --> 00:59:41,948
"I’ll be back in a moment with your pill. "

688
00:59:42,042 --> 00:59:47,831
