of them now and they’ve got pills.

695
01:00:21,247 --> 01:00:25,494
They’re going to turn you into one of them.
You’ve started already.

696
01:00:25,584 --> 01:00:29,997
You picked up a piece of broccoli and went,
"What a lovely piece of broccoli. "

697
01:00:30,089 --> 01:00:32,627
I can’t believe it.
It’s beyond disgusting.

698
01:00:36,136 --> 01:00:38,176
Snot face, please help.

699
01:00:45,020 --> 01:00:47,059
Come on.

700
01:00:50,317 --> 01:00:55,940
Look, remember when your dad picked up
the megabeast and threw her out the window?

701
01:00:56,030 --> 01:01:00,408
- That never happened.
- It didn’t happen, but you wanted it to.

702
01:01:01,578 --> 01:01:04,199
Yeah. So did I.

703
01:01:06,040 --> 01:01:08,911
Do you remember? Hm?

704
01:01:09,752 --> 01:01:11,579
Remember?

705
01:01:13,464 --> 01:01:17,711
Elizabeth, you’ve made
a mess of your beautiful hair.

706
01:01:19,470 --> 01:01:22,257
The time has come...

707
01:01:22,348 --> 01:01:27,175
when we don’t want to hear the words
Drop Dead Fred ever again.

708
01:01:28,312 --> 01:01:29,936
Don’t you agree, Nigel?

709
01:01:31,356 --> 01:01:35,817
- Hm? About what?
- This Drop Dead Fred business.

710
01:01:41,575 --> 01:01:45,952
- I’m sorry, Pol.
- Stand still. I’ll clean it later.

711
01:01:47,038 --> 01:01:49,078
I have some cereal?

712
01:01:49,165 --> 01:01:51,407
May I have some cereal?

713
01:01:51,501 --> 01:01:56,922
Yes, you may in just a minute.
We don’t eat food off the floor.

714
01:01:57,006 --> 01:02:01,715
- Why do you call him Drop Dead Fred?
- Because that’s his name, Daddy.

715
01:02:01,803 --> 01:02:05,670
And Drop Dead Fred
is going to teach me how to cook today.

716
01:02:05,765 --> 01:02:11,518
I’m going to need flour and sugar
and honey and vodka.

717
01:02:11,604 --> 01:02:15,304
And a pair of your pants.
We’re making pants pie.

718
01:02:15,399 --> 01:02:17,439
Ouch!

719
01:02:17,526 --> 01:02:21,061
Vodka and pants pie.
God knows what else.

720
01:02:21,989 --> 01:02:24,028
She’s only a kid, Pol.

721
01:02:25,409 --> 01:02:29,109
Daddy, how about we throw
Mommy out the window?

722
01:02:29,204 --> 01:02:33,036
It won’t hurt her.
She’ll land right in the gladioli’s.

723
01:02:35,294 --> 01:02:38,662
You shouldn’t say things like that
about your mother.

724
01:02:38,755 --> 01:02:40,997
She might cut your head off.

725
01:02:42,676 --> 01:02:44,715
Very funny, Elizabeth.

726
01:02:44,803 --> 01:02:48,337
Sometimes I think I don’t love you
as much as I used to.

727
01:02:48,431 --> 01:02:52,761
- Drop Dead Fred does.
- No more Drop Dead Fred, period!

728
01:02:55,897 --> 01:02:59,941
- Hi, Fred.
- You’re completely wrong cos I don’t love you.

729
01:03:00,026 --> 01:03:04,652
I don’t love anyone cos love’s
for girls and girls are disgusting.

730
01:03:04,739 --> 01:03:09,733
I’m a loner. I’m a crazy, wide-eyed loner
on a doomed space mission to Venus

731
01:03:09,827 --> 01:03:12,614
to battle with the three-headed megabeast.

732
01:03:12,705 --> 01:03:16,537
But on the way there, I caught cornflakes disease.

733
01:03:29,012 --> 01:03:33,970
Pants pie can’t save me now.
The only thing that can save me is a mud pie.

734
01:03:34,059 --> 01:03:35,886
Yeah! Come on.

735
01:03:44,903 --> 01:03:47,145
Here it comes.

736
01:03:47,238 --> 01:03:49,278
- Take the top off.
- OK.

737
01:03:49,365 --> 01:03:52,699
- Here it comes.
- Wow, my first real mud pie!

738
01:03:52,785 --> 01:03:59,748
It’s not ready yet. We need lots of other things.
We need cornflakes and orange juice. Beautiful.

739
01:04:00,626 --> 01:04:03,497
- That’s lovely.
- This is fun.

740
01:04:04,589 --> 01:04:07,673
A little tea. A lot of tea.

741
01:04:08,676 --> 01:04:11,214
- Sugar?
- Yeah.

742
01:04:11,303 --> 01:04:13,545
- That’s good.
- Here.

743
01:04:13,639 --> 01:04:17,423
That’s good. There’s the milk. Good.
Lots of milk.

744
01:04:18,519 --> 01:04:21,354
Lovely. Right.

745
01:04:22,690 --> 01:04:27,766
Yeah, but it’s not ready.
It’s still too pretty. It needs something.

746
01:04:27,861 --> 01:04:29,901
I know.

747
01:04:37,496 --> 01:04:38,954
There.

748
01:04:39,039 --> 01:04:44,625
Great. When something’s not working, the best
thing is to tear it apart to make it better.

749
01:04:44,711 --> 01:04:48,376
Elizabeth, are you behaving in there?

750
01:04:51,009 --> 01:04:54,093
- I’m not afraid of the megabeast.
- I’m not either.

751
01:04:54,178 --> 01:04:57,428
When she comes in here,
we’ll make her eat up this mud.

752
01:04:57,515 --> 01:05:00,765
- And then we’ll cut her head off.
- With scissors.

753
01:05:00,852 --> 01:05:04,552
- And then we’ll make her eat it.
- Make her eat her own head?

754
01:05:04,647 --> 01:05:08,514
- With what?
- Oh, yeah. Well, I’ll eat her head, then.

755
01:05:08,609 --> 01:05:12,654
- And I’ll eat the rest of her.
- Yeah! And then we’ll get up...

756
01:05:13,572 --> 01:05:18,779
And we’ll poo her all over the table
cos we’re not afraid of anything. Yeah!

757
01:05:18,869 --> 01:05:21,325
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

758
01:05:21,413 --> 01:05:22,528
Argh!

759
01:05:22,623 --> 01:05:25,493
- Elizabeth!
- Quick, hide.

760
01:05:25,584 --> 01:05:27,623
Quick.

761
01:05:29,087 --> 01:05:30,581
Hurry up!

762
01:05:33,800 --> 01:05:35,840
OK?

763
01:05:39,055 --> 01:05:40,882
Ah!

764
01:05:43,309 --> 01:05:45,101
Oh, my...

765
01:05:49,148 --> 01:05:51,556
What is wrong with you?

766
01:05:56,489 --> 01:05:59,443
You’ve been playing with him, haven’t you?

767
01:06:00,743 --> 01:06:02,783
Where is he?

768
01:06:06,123 --> 01:06:08,910
Don’t take him away from me!

769
01:06:09,001 --> 01:06:12,536
So that must make you cry.
Well, now I know what to do.

770
01:06:12,630 --> 01:06:17,872
Give me it. No, don’t take him away from me.

771
01:06:22,890 --> 01:06:25,131
- Nigel, do it.
- No, I won’t.

772
01:06:25,225 --> 01:06:30,432
- I don’t want anything to do with it. It’s not right.
- All right. I’ll do it.

773
01:06:39,656 --> 01:06:41,695
It’s not right.

774
01:06:41,783 --> 01:06:44,653
What would you know about raising a child?

775
01:06:51,918 --> 01:06:53,957
Apparently nothing.

776
01:06:57,965 --> 01:07:01,381
If you ever touch this again,
I’ll throw it in the trash.

777
01:07:01,469 --> 01:07:05,051
Do you know what will happen?
He will be crushed to death.

778
01:07:35,418 --> 01:07:38,752
"Dear Drop Dead Fred,

779
01:07:38,838 --> 01:07:46,051
"you were my only friend
but she took you away from me.

780
01:07:48,848 --> 01:07:52,548
"I know I’ll see you again someday. "

781
01:07:55,730 --> 01:07:59,858
"If you come back,
I promise we’ll run away together. "

782
01:07:59,942 --> 01:08:02,515
See that? "Promise. "

783
01:08:03,654 --> 01:08:06,738
I found that when I was
hiding in the garden shed.

784
01:08:06,824 --> 01:08:11,865
That’s right. That’s where I hid it.
But you never answered it.

785
01:08:13,997 --> 01:08:16,239
You just disappeared.

786
01:08:17,751 --> 01:08:22,212
And when you did all the... life

787
01:08:22,297 --> 01:08:25,215
and, um, the spirit...

788
01:08:25,884 --> 01:08:29,467
- and the...
- The Fred.

789
01:08:29,554 --> 01:08:34,015
Yeah, Fred. Just went out of me.

790
01:08:36,227 --> 01:08:40,688
I should never have let my mother know
how much she could hurt me.

791
01:08:42,317 --> 01:08:47,192
Once she knew how, she knew
that she could do it all the time.

792
01:08:47,280 --> 01:08:49,107
And she did.

793
01:08:53,911 --> 01:08:56,947
So I never showed
her my real feelings again.

794
01:09:01,585 --> 01:09:04,372
- So?
- So?

795
01:09:04,463 --> 01:09:06,503
So now can we run away, please?

796
01:09:08,300 --> 01:09:11,550
- Where to?
- To the party.

797
01:09:11,637 --> 01:09:14,673
- To the Charlie party.
- Yeah.

798
01:09:14,765 --> 01:09:16,176
- Yeah?
- Yeah!

799
01:09:16,266 --> 01:09:17,464
Yeah!

800
01:09:25,942 --> 01:09:27,567
OK?

801
01:09:27,652 --> 01:09:29,692
Let’s go.

802
01:09:30,405 --> 01:09:33,157
Oh, no, gladiolas.

803
01:09:34,200 --> 01:09:36,608
No. No. No!

804
01:09:48,005 --> 01:09:50,496
Where do you think you’re going?

805
01:09:50,591 --> 01:09:52,002
I’m going.

806
01:09:52,093 --> 01:09:57,051
- No, you’re not, you’re staying.
- No, Mother, this time I’m definitely going.

807
01:10:05,939 --> 01:10:07,979
Good night, flake.

808
01:10:10,736 --> 01:10:13,523
Yeah, well, we’re not scared of you, fatso.

809
01:10:15,198 --> 01:10:19,278
Come on. We’ll go out the window.
I’m good at this. Stand back.

810
01:10:24,291 --> 01:10:26,330
Wait a minute.

811
01:10:29,879 --> 01:10:31,919
I love those breaking noises.

812
01:10:32,924 --> 01:10:35,166
Let’s go. Come on.

813
01:10:38,054 --> 01:10:40,510
Hey, door-to-window service.

814
01:10:41,182 --> 01:10:43,638
- I brought your dress, madam.
- Mickey.

815
01:10:45,061 --> 01:10:48,512
- Can you give me a lift?
- Absolutely. Come on.

816
01:10:48,606 --> 01:10:50,017
Oi, wait for me.

817
01:10:56,739 --> 01:10:59,989
- I believe you ordered the spaghetti.
- I hate you.

818
01:11:00,075 --> 01:11:03,776
Mickey, I’m so sorry.
I hope I didn’t get you into trouble.

819
01:11:03,871 --> 01:11:07,121
No. Look, it’s OK.
It’s all been great to me.

820
01:11:08,083 --> 01:11:13,078
You’re going to look beautiful in your dress.
I hope Charles appreciates it.

821
01:11:13,171 --> 01:11:16,042
He’s just a total and utter girl, isn’t he?

822
01:11:16,133 --> 01:11:19,252
This is great,
stuck in a truck with two girls.

823
01:11:32,148 --> 01:11:34,556
Mickey, you’re the best.

824
01:11:37,487 --> 01:11:41,021
- Thanks.
- I think I was six when we moved away.

825
01:11:41,115 --> 01:11:46,738
I remember getting in the car, pulling away,
taking one last look at you

826
01:11:46,829 --> 01:11:51,123
and thinking, "I’m never going
to get to have fun with Betsy again. "

827
01:11:51,208 --> 01:11:52,833
Mickey Bunce.

828
01:11:53,878 --> 01:11:57,377
Don’t you hate it when you’re right
about the wrong things?

829
01:11:57,464 --> 01:12:00,668
- Let’s go.
- Thanks.

830
01:12:19,694 --> 01:12:22,944
- Snot face, you are looking great.
- I am?

831
01:12:23,031 --> 01:12:25,652
Yeah. For a girl.

832
01:12:36,586 --> 01:12:38,625
There he is.

833
01:12:41,716 --> 01:12:44,420
- Is that him?
- Mm-hm.

834
01:12:48,014 --> 01:12:52,474
I thought he liked wine.
Why does he keep spitting it out?

835
01:12:52,560 --> 01:12:55,430
- Where’s he gone?
- I don’t know. Come on.

836
01:12:55,521 --> 01:12:56,766
Right.

837
01:12:57,564 --> 01:13:01,479
- Fred, let’s just behave ourselves.
- Sure. Not a problem.

838
01:13:01,568 --> 01:13:03,395
Grapes.

839
01:13:04,488 --> 01:13:06,777
Could someone grab a hold of this?

840
01:13:09,743 --> 01:13:15,579
What? Why do I always get the blame? You’ve
got the grape. The lady with the grape did it.

841
01:13:22,964 --> 01:13:25,835
- Where is he?
- I don’t know.

842
01:13:25,925 --> 01:13:29,175
Don’t worry.
I’ll find Charlie boy for you.

843
01:13:29,262 --> 01:13:31,967
Wait here. Charlie!

844
01:13:33,599 --> 01:13:35,010
Charlie!

845
01:13:35,101 --> 01:13:36,429
Oha...

846
01:13:40,898 --> 01:13:42,807
No panties.

847
01:13:42,900 --> 01:13:44,857
No panties! Ah!

848
01:13:44,944 --> 01:13:48,443
Get up. Get up.

849
01:13:50,241 --> 01:13:51,865
- Fred, get up.
- Go away!

850
01:13:51,951 --> 01:13:54,192
- Get up.
- Spoilsport.

851
01:13:57,915 --> 01:14:00,750
I was just admiring your dress.

852
01:14:00,834 --> 01:14:04,583
The material, it’s so pretty. Slinky.

853
01:14:05,505 --> 01:14:07,083
Oh!

854
01:14:07,174 --> 01:14:09,961
- It’s pretty neat.
- It looks good on you.

855
01:14:10,052 --> 01:14:14,001
It feels good on.
I like yours. Yours is nice.

856
01:14:14,848 --> 01:14:17,553
- It’s very purple.
- Annabelle.

857
01:14:17,642 --> 01:14:20,180
- My little Chardonnay.
- There you are.

858
01:14:22,313 --> 01:14:26,393
Elizabeth. My God.

859
01:14:27,151 --> 01:14:29,191
That’s him.

860
01:14:29,904 --> 01:14:34,531
Don't just stand there, do something.
Go on. Kiss him.

861
01:14:39,664 --> 01:14:41,703
You said she was mousey.

862
01:14:44,251 --> 01:14:46,956
I’m sorry. Excuse me.

863
01:14:47,046 --> 01:14:49,085
Don’t go. It’s going great.

864
01:14:54,178 --> 01:14:56,217
Are you OK?

865
01:14:57,139 --> 01:14:59,178
- I think so.
- Yeah?

866
01:14:59,266 --> 01:15:01,259
Yeah.

867
01:15:01,351 --> 01:15:05,894
- My little vermentino.
- My little Pinot Noir.

868
01:15:08,734 --> 01:15:13,609
I can’t believe we left the party so soon.
All that wine to spit around.

869
01:15:13,697 --> 01:15:17,860
- We didn’t even get to play spin the bottle.
- I got upset.

870
01:15:17,951 --> 01:15:22,577
God, you’re so stupid.
You never leave a party till the very end.

871
01:15:22,664 --> 01:15:26,115
- Really?
- Yeah, really.

872
01:15:26,209 --> 01:15:28,830
Cinderella left early. Remember her?

873
01:15:28,920 --> 01:15:33,546
No, I don’t remember her. I forgot
everything about her. She made me puke.

874
01:15:33,633 --> 01:15:36,752
I remember the ugly sisters.
They were great.

875
01:15:39,472 --> 01:15:41,511
You’re here.

876
01:15:42,600 --> 01:15:46,218
- I tell you something?
- What?

877
01:15:46,312 --> 01:15:49,562
You look fabulous.

878
01:15:50,941 --> 01:15:52,768
I do?

879
01:15:53,861 --> 01:15:56,102
Darling, you need me.

880
01:15:57,114 --> 01:15:59,153
I do?

881
01:16:00,325 --> 01:16:02,365
To protect you.

882
01:16:03,328 --> 01:16:05,368
From what?

883
01:16:06,832 --> 01:16:09,073
Men like me.

884
01:16:10,752 --> 01:16:14,880
- But, Charles, there’s so many things...
- No. No talk.

885
01:16:14,964 --> 01:16:17,004
Just kiss.

886
01:16:31,439 --> 01:16:33,478
What was that?

887
01:16:33,566 --> 01:16:36,401
Oh, it’s Fred.

888
01:16:36,485 --> 01:16:40,400
Fred? What did you do,
give this Fred a key?

889
01:16:40,489 --> 01:16:45,484
Hey, Fred, I’m home now.
It’s Charles, Lizzie's husband.

890
01:16:49,498 --> 01:16:51,538
Is he the violent type?

891
01:16:51,625 --> 01:16:54,033
Only with me.

892
01:16:54,128 --> 01:16:55,586
Jesus.

893
01:17:04,805 --> 01:17:09,348
Who does this guy think he is,
playing around with a married woman?

894
01:17:21,321 --> 01:17:23,147
Polly, hi.

895
01:17:23,239 --> 01:17:25,279
What did you do?

896
01:17:26,492 --> 01:17:28,532
Hello?

897
01:17:29,203 --> 01:17:32,738
You are a wonderful man, Charles,
but she is dangerous.

898
01:17:32,832 --> 01:17:37,826
I love dangerous. Don’t worry.
I can take care of this Drop Dead Fred.

899
01:17:37,920 --> 01:17:40,541
If you think you can handle it, here.

900
01:17:40,631 --> 01:17:45,174
- But, Charles, she is just a child.
- I’m a grown-up, Polly.

901
01:17:47,763 --> 01:17:49,802
Where were we?

902
01:17:52,643 --> 01:17:55,098
Eurgh!
What does that taste like?

903
01:17:55,187 --> 01:17:58,638
Charles, let’s talk.
It’s kind of important to me.

904
01:17:58,732 --> 01:18:00,771
Of course it is.

905
01:18:04,321 --> 01:18:07,606
- You’re not going to get that out, are you?
- Not now.

906
01:18:07,699 --> 01:18:09,738
- Not now?
- No, I mean now.

907
01:18:09,826 --> 01:18:11,866
- Now.
- Now.

908
01:18:14,038 --> 01:18:15,865
Hang on.

909
01:18:15,957 --> 01:18:21,960
Hang on. This isn’t how the pigeons do it. You’re
supposed to stamp on her head and peck her.

910
01:18:22,046 --> 01:18:25,213
- Charles.
- Annabelle.

911
01:18:25,299 --> 01:18:27,339
- What?
- What?

912
01:18:27,426 --> 01:18:29,964
What happened?

913
01:18:30,054 --> 01:18:32,462
You just said Annabelle.

914
01:18:32,556 --> 01:18:35,925
- No, I didn’t.
- Yes, you did. You said, "Oh, Annabelle. "

915
01:18:36,018 --> 01:18:39,683
- You said "Oh, Annabelle. "
- That’s impossible.

916
01:18:39,772 --> 01:18:43,022
Charles, I heard you. You said Annabelle.

917
01:18:43,108 --> 01:18:51,116
Well... if I said, "Oh, Annabelle," isn’t it better
that I said, "Oh, Annabelle" and I was here with you,

918
01:18:51,200 --> 01:18:55,328
than to say "Oh, Lizzie" and be
somewhere else with Annabelle?

919
01:18:58,206 --> 01:19:00,033
Yeah.

920
01:19:03,003 --> 01:19:07,997
I know what you’re doing. You’re going to do
what he did to Annabelle on the sofa.

921
01:19:08,091 --> 01:19:11,791
- Don’t say things like that now, Fred.
- Lizzie.

922
01:19:11,886 --> 01:19:19,099
I think it’s time to
say goodbye... to your friend.

923
01:19:21,229 --> 01:19:23,352
Hey. Hey!

924
01:19:24,482 --> 01:19:27,898
Listen, I’m Drop Dead Fred, right?

925
01:19:27,985 --> 01:19:34,355
If your husband thinks he can get rid of me with
a stupid pill, he’s got another think coming.

926
01:19:35,284 --> 01:19:37,111
Ow.

927
01:19:38,996 --> 01:19:41,701
Well, thank you very much,
dear friend.

928
01:19:45,794 --> 01:19:47,621
Charles.

929
01:19:48,505 --> 01:19:51,174
Oh, you look so handsome!

930
01:19:51,258 --> 01:19:55,635
- Lizzie, come on, now. Don’t do that.
- We have to do it this way.

931
01:19:55,721 --> 01:19:57,760
Look, I’ve got a long day.

932
01:19:58,849 --> 01:20:00,888
I don’t like him.

933
01:20:04,896 --> 01:20:06,972
No. It scares me.

934
01:20:08,108 --> 01:20:10,147
Go on. Out his throat.

935
01:20:11,694 --> 01:20:13,901
Go on.

936
01:20:20,411 --> 01:20:24,076
- What’s the news?
- Wait till my endorphins kick in.

937
01:20:24,165 --> 01:20:28,412
You know, the body’s natural morphine.
Here it comes.

938
01:20:28,502 --> 01:20:30,294
Ooh!

939
01:20:30,379 --> 01:20:33,997
- The aerobic rush. Now ask me.
- What’s the big news?

940
01:20:36,635 --> 01:20:40,929
Have you ever seen so many zeros
outside of the national debt?

941
01:20:41,890 --> 01:20:46,683
- I never knew a barge was worth this much?
- Not a barge. A river condominium.

942
01:20:46,770 --> 01:20:50,471
I had no idea they were worth
that much until mine sank.

943
01:20:50,565 --> 01:20:54,777
What a total groove. You’ve got Charles
back and I have all those zeros.

944
01:20:54,861 --> 01:20:58,230
Our lives have worked out!
Thank you, Drop Dead Fred.

945
01:20:58,323 --> 01:21:01,193
Don’t waste your breath.
I’m phasing him out.

946
01:21:01,284 --> 01:21:03,526
- Really?
- Yeah.

947
01:21:03,620 --> 01:21:06,989
What’s for dinner?
Your favourite.

948
01:21:07,081 --> 01:21:09,703
Beef Wellington, how nice.

949
01:21:13,755 --> 01:21:17,005
- To us.
- To... us.

950
01:21:22,805 --> 01:21:24,845
For you, my love.

951
01:21:31,772 --> 01:21:34,393
What the hell is that?

952
01:21:36,443 --> 01:21:39,693
- Mud pie.
- Is that supposed to be a joke?

953
01:21:39,780 --> 01:21:44,027
- Fred!
- It’s either him or me, Elizabeth.

954
01:21:44,117 --> 01:21:49,906
It’s you. I swear. Fred is gone.
You know what? I’ll make a dinner salad.

955
01:21:49,998 --> 01:21:53,248
- Forget it.
- I’ll make a lovely salad. Please.

956
01:21:53,335 --> 01:21:59,005
It’ll be the most romantic, wonderful,
romantic... romantic salad.

957
01:21:59,090 --> 01:22:02,293
- A romantic dinner salad.
- Yeah. OK?

958
01:22:02,385 --> 01:22:04,841
- OK.
- Here I go. I’m making it.

959
01:22:07,056 --> 01:22:12,726
It’s going to be so good. If you leave those pants,
I’ll take them to the dry cleaners tomorrow.

960
01:22:12,812 --> 01:22:15,054
You’ll never hear from Fred again.

961
01:22:21,821 --> 01:22:25,237
- He’s the wrong man for you.
- I don’t want to hear it.

962
01:22:25,324 --> 01:22:27,364
You’re not happy.

963
01:22:28,536 --> 01:22:33,778
- Yes, I am.
- If you’re so happy, why am I still here?

964
01:22:35,292 --> 01:22:37,332
I can fix that.

965
01:22:38,128 --> 01:22:40,833
No, don’t do that.
Please don’t do that.

966
01:22:56,980 --> 01:22:59,601
Darling...

967
01:22:59,691 --> 01:23:02,857
Of course I still love you, Annabelle.

968
01:23:02,944 --> 01:23:06,942
Hey, I’m your fella, Annabelle.

969
01:23:07,031 --> 01:23:09,071
Yeah.

970
01:23:09,158 --> 01:23:11,317
Snot face, come here.

971
01:23:12,036 --> 01:23:16,663
- I don’t hear you.
- It’s important. He’s worse than the megabeast.

972
01:23:17,750 --> 01:23:21,582
- That’s it. I’m taking the last pill.
- No.

973
01:23:21,671 --> 01:23:24,458
- The goodbye pill.
- Don’t do that.

974
01:23:28,219 --> 01:23:30,544
Just look in there. Please.

975
01:23:35,059 --> 01:23:38,262
Annabelle... Annabelle, she’ll never know.

976
01:23:39,396 --> 01:23:41,436
And so what if she does?

977
01:23:42,566 --> 01:23:47,808
No, listen. Would you listen?
I am in control with Lizzie.

978
01:23:47,904 --> 01:23:50,312
I’m in the driver’s seat.

979
01:23:50,407 --> 01:23:52,446
She trusts me.

980
01:23:55,203 --> 01:23:57,243
You’ve got to leave him.

981
01:23:58,206 --> 01:24:00,033
I don’t feel so good.

982
01:24:00,792 --> 01:24:02,416
Leave him.

983
01:24:03,962 --> 01:24:06,001
I can’t.

984
01:24:07,590 --> 01:24:09,417
I’m scared to be alone.

985
01:24:11,886 --> 01:24:13,925
Come with me.

986
01:24:32,948 --> 01:24:36,068
- "Fred?"
- "Yeah. "

987
01:24:36,160 --> 01:24:39,991
- "Where are we going?"
- "Use your imagination. "

988
01:24:42,541 --> 01:24:45,411
- "Fred?"
- "You’ll know what to do. "

989
01:24:47,712 --> 01:24:49,752
"Fred?"

990
01:25:12,945 --> 01:25:15,353
I’m scared.

991
01:25:15,448 --> 01:25:17,689
I don’t want to be alone here.

992
01:25:53,234 --> 01:25:57,279
Get in, Lizzie.
I want to take you away, goose.

993
01:25:58,740 --> 01:26:00,566
Don’t you love me anymore?

994
01:26:05,580 --> 01:26:08,367
- Hi.
- Fred.

995
01:26:12,378 --> 01:26:14,833
So what are you going to do about him?

996
01:26:33,565 --> 01:26:36,601
Nice job.
Nice job.

997
01:26:36,693 --> 01:26:40,607
Couldn’t have done better myself.
Come on. This way.

998
01:26:42,407 --> 01:26:43,985
Ow!

999
01:26:49,956 --> 01:26:51,996
We need a tree.

1000
01:27:21,946 --> 01:27:25,196
You’re getting good at this. Let’s go.

1001
01:27:41,798 --> 01:27:44,419
Just where do you think you’re going?

1002
01:27:45,302 --> 01:27:48,172
Just forget her.
Just say the magic words.

1003
01:27:49,597 --> 01:27:53,215
- I’m not afraid of you.
- You can’t go in there.

1004
01:27:53,893 --> 01:27:56,052
I’m not afraid of you!

1005
01:27:56,145 --> 01:27:58,019
Finally, the magic words.

1006
01:28:43,483 --> 01:28:45,855
We don’t have to be afraid any more.

1007
01:29:01,667 --> 01:29:04,123
You have to go now.

1008
01:29:12,887 --> 01:29:15,971
OK. I’m ready.

1009
01:29:18,017 --> 01:29:20,258
- Let’s go.
- No.

1010
01:29:22,604 --> 01:29:25,391
You have to go alone.

1011
01:29:25,482 --> 01:29:29,396
- But I want you to come back with me.
- That’s just tough.

1012
01:29:30,320 --> 01:29:34,021
You have to go alone. I can’t get back now.

1013
01:29:37,118 --> 01:29:39,158
Look, you’ve got you now.

1014
01:29:40,205 --> 01:29:43,455
You don’t need me. Not anymore.

1015
01:29:45,376 --> 01:29:48,128
So...

1016
01:29:48,213 --> 01:29:50,039
goodbye.

1017
01:29:56,387 --> 01:29:59,637
Just kiss me and say Drop Dead Fred.

1018
01:30:02,310 --> 01:30:04,349
Now.

1019
01:30:05,479 --> 01:30:07,519
Drop Dead Fred.

1020
01:31:07,790 --> 01:31:12,167
What do you mean it’s no good
for you this way? Annabelle, wait.

1021
01:31:14,755 --> 01:31:17,127
Well, to hell with you, Annabelle.

1022
01:31:21,303 --> 01:31:25,347
Lizzie, is our romantic salad ready?

1023
01:31:25,432 --> 01:31:27,555
Yeah.

1024
01:31:38,153 --> 01:31:40,192
Bye, Charles.

1025
01:31:40,280 --> 01:31:42,106
Oh!

1026
01:31:42,198 --> 01:31:44,321
I forgot to give you something.

1027
01:32:28,577 --> 01:32:31,910
Yes, Charles.
Leave everything to me. It’s Charles.

1028
01:32:31,997 --> 01:32:33,621
Charles?

1029
01:32:36,584 --> 01:32:39,704
Young lady,
you have a lot of explaining to do.

1030
01:32:39,796 --> 01:32:45,252
I know what’s best for me. You have
to stop treating me like I’m your enemy.

1031
01:32:45,343 --> 01:32:49,127
Enemy? Sometimes I wonder with you.

1032
01:32:49,222 --> 01:32:51,629
I made the same mistake
a lot of people make.

1033
01:32:51,724 --> 01:32:55,342
- I had a child to save a marriage.
- How can you say that?

1034
01:32:55,436 --> 01:32:58,105
You made things worse.
He left because of you.

1035
01:33:00,316 --> 01:33:02,143
What a pile of shit.

1036
01:33:04,153 --> 01:33:09,395
Don’t you dare.
Don’t you dare walk out on me.

1037
01:33:10,325 --> 01:33:13,161
Elizabeth. Lizzie.

1038
01:33:14,288 --> 01:33:16,327
I’ll be lonely.

1039
01:33:46,819 --> 01:33:49,108
You should get yourself a friend.

1040
01:34:05,796 --> 01:34:08,750
You have a lot of options
open to you right now.

1041
01:34:08,841 --> 01:34:12,007
I just think I’d like
to be one of them. OK?

1042
01:34:13,679 --> 01:34:17,379
- OK.
- Daddy, it was his idea.

1043
01:34:17,474 --> 01:34:21,472
I wanted to play but he bumped me
on the head and said piss off.

1044
01:34:21,561 --> 01:34:25,606
- Natalie, what did you do?
- Natalie Bunce, where are you?

1045
01:34:25,690 --> 01:34:28,940
Come back in here this minute
and get cleaned up.

1046
01:34:29,027 --> 01:34:31,066
Natalie, what happened here?

1047
01:34:31,154 --> 01:34:35,531
- It’s chocolate and it’s yummy. Want some?
- No, I don’t want any.

1048
01:34:35,617 --> 01:34:41,406
She made a terrible mess in the kitchen and
expects me to believe a pretend friend did it.

1049
01:34:41,497 --> 01:34:45,115
He’s not pretend.
He’s Drop Dead Fred.

1050
01:34:47,712 --> 01:34:49,751
What did you say?

1051
01:34:49,839 --> 01:34:53,255
She said I’m not pretend.
What are you, deaf?

1052
01:34:53,342 --> 01:34:56,592
Natalie, now, come on.
What really happened?

1053
01:34:56,679 --> 01:34:59,929
I told you.
Don’t you believe me?

1054
01:35:00,015 --> 01:35:05,602
I believe you. Next time you see
Drop Dead Fred, you send him my love.

1055
01:35:06,230 --> 01:35:08,021
Mr Bunce.

1056
01:35:08,107 --> 01:35:11,807
Look out. It’s the witch.
Come on. Quick.

1057
01:35:12,986 --> 01:35:17,778
This is it. I’m afraid you’re going
to have to find a new baby-sitter.

1058
01:35:17,866 --> 01:35:19,905
She’s just too much.

1059
01:35:20,827 --> 01:35:22,701
OK. Now.

1060
01:35:28,668 --> 01:35:31,503
Help! Help!

1061
01:35:32,547 --> 01:35:35,252
We did it.
I told you it would work. Brilliant.

1062
01:35:37,385 --> 01:35:40,635
Help! Help! Help!

1063
01:35:42,932 --> 01:35:44,723
Well done.

